r\n|{{Party shading/Libertarian}} |[[Libertarian Party (United States)|Libertarian]]\n|{{Party shading/Libertarian}} |6,116\n|{{Party shading/Libertarian}} |2.77%\n|\n|{{Party shading/Constitution}} |David Ryon\n|{{Party shading/Constitution}} |[[Constitution Party (United States)|Constitution]]\n|{{Party shading/Constitution}} |3,887\n|{{Party shading/Constitution}} |1.76%\n|**\n|-\n|2012\n|[[United States House of Representatives|U.S. House of Representatives]]\n|[[General election (U.S.)|General]]\n|\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |'''Steve Stivers'''\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |205,277\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |61.56%\n|\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Pat Lang\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |128,188\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |38.44%\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>Write-in candidate Travis Casper received 6 votes (<1%) <br>\n<nowiki>**</nowiki>Write-in candidate Bill Buckel received 45 votes (0.02%)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://stivers.house.gov/ Congressman Steve Stivers] official U.S. House site\n*[http://www.stivers4congress.com/ Steve Stivers for Congress] \n*{{Dmoz|Regional/North_America/United_States/Ohio/Government/Federal/US_House_of_Representatives/Steve_Stivers_%5BR-15%5D|Steve Stivers}}\n*{{CongLinks | congbio = S001187 | votesmart = 45333 | ballot = Steve_Stivers | govtrack = 412461 | opencong = 412461 | rollcall = 27951 | politifact = | ontheissues = OH/Steve_Stivers.htm | congress = steve-stivers/2047 | fec = H8OH15076 | opensecrets = N00029574 | assets = steve-stivers | legistorm = 2782/Rep_Steve_Stivers_OH.html | followthemoney = 6555 | c-span = stevestivers02 | imdb = | bloomberg = | nyt = | washpo = gIQA88sTKP }}\n*[http://thehill.com/resources/lawmaker-ratings/150227-rep-steve-stivers-r-ohio-15th Lawmaker ratings] at ''[[The Hill (newspa